The multiplicity of the Operation element with the GetTile operation metadata is wrong.
The response format ({responseformat}) is distinct to the requested format ({requestedformat}) for the '{layerid}' layer.
At least one Format must be provided with value 'image/png' or 'image/gif' for the '{layerid}' layer.

Check manually that the language of the Abstract element content matches with the language of the Capabilities document.

Check manually that the data is provided using at least one geographical coordinate system based on ETRS89 in continental Europe and ITRS outside continental Europe. Check manually that the TileMatrixSet has either no SupportedCRS element or one that matches the CRS identifier of one of the ETRS89 based or ITRS based coordinate systems.
Check manually that the language of the texts included in the legend match with the requested language.

The GetTileOperation check is automatic only for InspireCRS84Quad TileMatrixSet (that is a INSPIRE recommendation). It has not been found in the service capabilities document. Check manually that the GetTile operation is implemented. Check that a GetTile request can be done and that a valid response is returned.

The GetTileOperation check is automatic only for InspireCRS84Quad TileMatrixSet (that is a INSPIRE recommendation). It has not been found in the service capabilities document. Check manually that "service", "request" and "language" parameters are implemented for the GetTile operation.

The GetTile Operation parameters implementation check is automatic only for InspireCRS84Quad TileMatrixSet (that is a INSPIRE recommendation). It has not been found in the service capabilities document. Check manually that "service", "request", "version", "layer", "style", "format", "tilematrixset", "tilematrix", "tilecol" and "tilerow" parameters are mandatory for the GetTile operation.

The GetTile Operation request is automatic only for InspireCRS84Quad TileMatrixSet (that is a INSPIRE recommendation). It has not been found in the service capabilities document. Check manually that the all layers get tile operation implements one of the mandatory formats ('image/png' or'image/gif').
